030/**
031 * Subclass of {@link Parser} for byte-based parsers.
032 *
033 * <h5 class='topic'>Description</h5>
034 * <p>
035 * This class is typically the parent class of all character-based parsers.
036 * It has 1 abstract method to implement on the session object...
037 * <ul>
038 *    <li><c>parse(ParserSession, ClassMeta)</c>
039 * </ul>
040 *
041 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
042 *    <li class='note'>This class is thread safe and reusable.
043 * </ul>
044 *
045 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
046 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/SerializersAndParsers">Serializers and Parsers</a>
047
048 * </ul>
049 */
050public class InputStreamParser extends Parser {
051

063   }

126      /**
127       * <i><l>InputStreamParser</l> configuration property:&emsp;</i>  Binary input format.
128       *
129       * <p>
130       * When using the {@link InputStreamParser#parse(Object,Class)} method on stream-based parsers and the input is a string, this defines the format to use
131       * when converting the string into a byte array.
132       *
133       * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
134       * <p class='bjava'>
135       *    <jc>// Create a parser that parses from BASE64.</jc>
136       *    InputStreamParser <jv>parser</jv> = MsgPackParser
137       *       .<jsm>create</jsm>()
138       *       .binaryFormat(<jsf>BASE64</jsf>)
139       *       .build();
140       *
141       *    String <jv>input</jv> = <js>"base64-encoded-string"</js>;
142       *
143       *    MyBean <jv>myBean</jv> = <jv>parser</jv>.parse(<jv>input</jv> , MyBean.<jk>class</jk>);
144       * </p>
145       *
146       * @param value
147       *    The new value for this property.
148       *    <br>The default value is {@link BinaryFormat#HEX}.
149       * @return This object.
150       */
151      @FluentSetter
152      public Builder binaryFormat(BinaryFormat value) {
153         binaryFormat = value;
154         return this;
155      }

648   //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
649   // Instance
650   //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
651
652   final BinaryFormat binaryFormat;
653
654   /**
655    * Constructor.
656    *
657    * @param builder The builder for this object.
658    */
659   protected InputStreamParser(Builder builder) {
660      super(builder);
661      binaryFormat = builder.binaryFormat;
662   }
663
664   @Override /* Parser */
665   public final boolean isReaderParser() {
666      return false;
667   }
668
669   @Override /* Context */
670   public InputStreamParserSession.Builder createSession() {
671      return InputStreamParserSession.create(this);
672   }
673
674   @Override /* Context */
675   public InputStreamParserSession getSession() {
676      return createSession().build();
677   }

683   /**
684    * Binary input format.
685    *
686    * @see Builder#binaryFormat(BinaryFormat)
687    * @return
688    *    The format to use when converting strings to byte arrays.
689    */
690   protected final BinaryFormat getBinaryFormat() {
691      return binaryFormat;
692   }

699   protected JsonMap properties() {
